The aggregates used in mixtures are by volume
the major constituents of the concrete mix.
They signicantly inuence the performance
and cost. Use only reputable suppliers whose
quality consistency can be relied on.
Sand should be free of organic matte such as
roots, twigs and leaves. Well graded sand
ranging from dust to coarse particles
will produce the best results - too many nes
will require a high water demand which causes
shrinkage during drying, while a no nes sand
results in a harsh mix with no workability.
SAND:
Use the least amount of water in the mix for the
workability required.
WATER:
The quantity of the mix should be small enough
to be used up within two hours -
NEVER re-temper a mix by mixing in
TIME:
additional water!
